        <hl1>TODAY IN BUSINESS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By MATTHEW L. WALD</byline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The owner of an Ohio nuclear plant has asked its insurer to pay for two years of lost production because of corrosion that it called ''unexpected and unforeseeable,'' even though it had resisted government pressure to inspect for acid leaks just before the problem was uncovered in 2002.</p>
        <p>MATTHEW L. WALD</p>
      </block>
